<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="459" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="64.[2003,2595,2307,2725]" pageId="64" pageNumber="459">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1924" box="[2159,2266,2417,2450]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Solisorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Solisorex</taxonomicName>
, phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kelaart" authorityYear="1852" box="[2040,2158,2456,2489]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Feroculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Feroculus</taxonomicName>
is uncertain, and a recent phy- logenetic study placed it in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ehrenberg" authorityYear="1832" box="[2388,2480,2495,2528]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Suncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Suncus</taxonomicName>
sister to a clade including S. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[2304,2357,2534,2567]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Suncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dayi">dayi</taxonomicName>
, S. 
<taxonomicName box="[2415,2522,2534,2567]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Suncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="murinus">murinus</taxonomicName>
, and S. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Anderson" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[2046,2198,2574,2607]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Suncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stoliczkanus">stoliczkanus</taxonomicName>
, although morphologically 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kelaart" authorityYear="1852" box="[2003,2122,2613,2646]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Feroculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Feroculus</taxonomicName>
has an uncanny resemblance to 
<taxonomicName box="[2006,2128,2653,2686]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sylvisorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sylvisorex</taxonomicName>
. In 1997, a population was discovered in southern India that was one of the
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="64.[1392,2597,2732,3041]" pageId="64" pageNumber="459">
first records of the species outside of Sri Lanka, although its presence in the Palni Hills of southern India was mentioned by W. T. Blanford in 1888. These disjunct populations potentially represent distinct species, although no taxonomic studies have been performed on either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kelaart" authorityYear="1852" box="[1694,1813,2851,2884]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Feroculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Feroculus</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1924" box="[1860,1967,2851,2884]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Solisorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Solisorex</taxonomicName>
in recent times. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
