<subSubSection lastPageId="65" lastPageNumber="460" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="64.[1392,2597,2732,3041]" pageId="64" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1392,1646,2938,2963]" pageId="64" pageNumber="459">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 98-118 mm, tail 65-73 mm, ear 8-10 mm, hindfoot 19-20 mm. Nospecific data are available for body weight. Kelaart’s Long-clawed Shrew is a large (smaller than Pearson’s Long-clawed Shrew, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1924" box="[2181,2405,3008,3041]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Solisorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="64" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pearsoni">Solisorex pearsoni</taxonomicName>
) and unique
</paragraph>
